
Overview of verb bristle

The verb bristle has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (3) abound, burst, bristle -- (be in a state of movement or action; "The room abounded with screaming children"; "The garden bristled with toddlers")
2. (2) bristle, uprise, stand up -- (rise up as in fear; "The dog's fur bristled"; "It was a sight to make one's hair uprise!")
3. bristle -- (have or be thickly covered with or as if with bristles; "bristling leaves")
4. bristle -- (react in an offended or angry manner; "He bristled at her suggestion that he should teach her how to use the program")
